      "text": "Under the idealized conditions of the [[first welfare theorem]], a system of [[free market]]s, also called a \"[[competitive equilibrium]],\" leads to a Pareto-efficient outcome. It was first demonstrated mathematically by economists [[Kenneth Arrow]] and [[Gérard Debreu]]."
    },
